									<h2 class="font-bold">DAY 1</h2>
									<p>We start the program at 9 am, with an opening prayer,
										singing our national anthem and introducing our speaker, Ms.
										Lanie C. Rallos which her area of expertise is on Video
										production, multimedia, and capstone track / thesis projects.
										Our speaker start by introducing herself and then we also
										introduce ourselves to her by telling our nicknames, area of
										expertise and the number of years as an educators.</p>
									<p>Most guest says that they have been teaching for years
										and some are just getting started as an educator. As we go
										along to the topic we acquire more knowledge about who are the
										21st century learners and How can we teach them that they may
										be able to understand and be attentive and productive to the
										class?</p>
									<p>After the discussions about the characteristics and
										behaviors of learners, the speaker held a group activity which
										consist of 3-4 members. As a group, members should list down
										their top 5 characteristic of student they encounter. And
										present it in front of the participants.</p>
									<p>Ms. Lai continued to discuss how challenging learners of
										this generations to us educators because of technology. She
										discussed some strategies and techniques she uses and share it
										in the seminar. Another group activity takes place. In the
										second activity, members must discussed and lists the best
										practices that they uses and share them to the other groups.
										The end of the Day 1 event brings us understanding about our
										learners and we acquire some strategies that we can apply to
										our learners.</p>
